course_aims:
This course aims to:
oﾠﾠ introduce students to the interdisciplinary nature of modern science;

oﾠﾠ instil an appreciation of the quantitative skills required for the practice of modern science, regardless of discipline;
oﾠﾠ improve students’ mathematical and computer programming skills in the context of scientific problems and issues;
oﾠﾠ demonstrate the importance of formulating and applying quantitative models of various phenomena in science;
oﾠﾠ introduce students to philosophical issues in science,ﾠincluding core activities which comprise science and someﾠfundamental aspects of scientific reasoning;
oﾠﾠ improve students’ skills in scientific communication and quantitative reasoning;
oﾠﾠ involve students in analysis of some “big picture” issues in science; and
oﾠﾠ engage students in the UQ “science community”.
